  "_doc": "Single source of truth for atom-built 9-slice frames. Read by the Node bake (scripts/nine-slice-kit.mjs), the in-app editor (NineSliceEditor), and the catalog edit-link (AssetLibraryStudio). Add a frame here and it becomes bakeable, editable, and catalog-linked with no other code change. atoms = names in public/assets/ui/kit/atoms; variants[].out = composed PNG in public/assets/ui/kit; swap = palette name; consume = the CSS var its content drives; carve = flood navy bleed outside the rail; line = filename of the transparent-interior 'line' twin baked into public/assets/ui/explore/frames (full ornament over a see-through center — assembled from the corner+edge atoms with a transparent fill; no masking, no carve — the fix for the 9-slice fill problem so a surface shows behind the chrome while the frame stays; the ornament must reach the element edge, so only bracket frames qualify, NOT the inset steel row rail; see ADR-0034).",
